## TRACKING & OPTIMIZATION

### Metrics to Track

**Article-Level:**
- Views per article
- Time on page
- Click-through to next article
- Click-through to CTA (free audit, strategy call, paid)
- Conversion rate by article

**Homepage-Level:**
- Which article links are clicked most?
- Do article links increase homepage dwell time?
- Do article links increase conversion rate?
- Which article attracts best quality leads?

### Optimization Rules

**If article gets high views but low CTAs:**
→ Strengthen CTA at end of article
→ Add CTA mid-article
→ Change CTA copy

**If article gets high views but doesn't lead to next article:**
→ Add "next article" recommendation at end
→ Improve internal linking between related articles
→ Create article series/path

**If certain article drives best quality leads:**
→ Promote that article more
→ Link to it more prominently on homepage
→ Create follow-up content on that topic

---

## THE FINAL HOMEPAGE FLOW (With Articles Integrated)

**CURRENT FLOW:**
Problem → Systems → Pricing → CTA

**NEW FLOW (With Articles):**
Problem → Read Article 1 (deep dive)
→ Systems (teasers, links to full articles)
→ Authority Section (links to all research)
→ Pricing (linked to relevant articles)
→ FAQ (article links answer objections)
→ Final CTA (article hub + direct actions)

**Result:**
- Every section has a clear learning/deepening path
- Visitors can go as deep as they want
- Self-qualifying: serious researchers find articles, time-crunched visitors go straight to CTA
- Authority compounded through research availability

